{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567192","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567192"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:56:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:56:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18943"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18943","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18943"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.2,0.25,0.15,0.34,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11677"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111026"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11677","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11677"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18943"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93143"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"15"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"3679"},{"type":"tags","id":"4748"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4969"},{"type":"tags","id":"4970"},{"type":"tags","id":"4983"},{"type":"tags","id":"6442"},{"type":"tags","id":"6446"},{"type":"tags","id":"11456"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11643"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27477"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37201"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41290"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43710"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44437"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111026","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/111026"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 55-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-day history of urethral discharge and dysuria. He denies urinary frequency, fever, or lower abdominal pain. He has been sexually active with a new female partner and has no sexual history with men. He does not identify as Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHis medical history includes depression, osteoarthritis, hypertension, type 2 diabetes mellitus, and benign prostatic hyperplasia. His regular medications include metformin, perindopril, and tamsulosin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is a clear urethral discharge. The prostate feels smooth and normal on digital rectal examination. Urinalysis reveals white cells but no nitrites. First-pass urine and urethral swab specimens have been collected for microscopy, culture, and nucleic acid amplification testing.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Azithromycin single dose","Ceftriaxone single dose","Await culture results before treating","Doxycycline for seven days","Ciprofloxacin for seven days"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with symptoms and signs consistent with non-gonococcal urethritis. The discharge has been clear throughout, which is typical for non-gonococcal causes such as \u003Cem\u003EChlamydia trachomatis\u003C/em\u003E or \u003Cem\u003EMycoplasma genitalium\u003C/em\u003E. Urinalysis showing white cells without nitrites supports a diagnosis of urethritis rather than a urinary tract infection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDoxycycline for seven days\u003C/strong\u003E is the recommended first-line empiric therapy for non-gonococcal urethritis. It is effective against \u003Cem\u003EChlamydia trachomatis\u003C/em\u003E and \u003Cem\u003EMycoplasma genitalium\u003C/em\u003E, the most common causative organisms. Empiric treatment should be started while awaiting test results to prevent complications and reduce transmission risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAzithromycin single dose\u003C/strong\u003E was previously used as first-line therapy, but increasing resistance, especially in \u003Cem\u003EMycoplasma genitalium\u003C/em\u003E, has led to a shift away from this regimen. It may be considered if doxycycline is contraindicated.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECiprofloxacin for seven days\u003C/strong\u003E is not recommended for empiric treatment of urethritis due to high resistance rates and poor coverage of the most likely pathogens.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAwait culture results before treating\u003C/strong\u003E would delay appropriate therapy and allow for ongoing transmission. The clinical presentation is sufficient to warrant empiric treatment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECeftriaxone single dose\u003C/strong\u003E is indicated for gonococcal urethritis, which typically presents with a copious, purulent discharge. In this case, the discharge is clear and non-purulent, making gonorrhoea less likely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EManagement should also include sexual health counselling, partner notification, and advice to abstain from sexual activity during treatment. Follow-up is important to review results and ensure symptom resolution.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Doxycycline is first-line empiric therapy for non-gonococcal urethritis while awaiting culture results.","Gonococcal urethritis typically presents with copious, purulent discharge, whereas non-gonococcal urethritis is often clear and less profuse.","Empiric treatment should not be delayed while awaiting results in symptomatic urethritis."],"references":["Ong JJ, Bourne C, Dean JA, Ryder N, Cornelisse VJ, Murray S, Kenchington P, Moten A, Gibbs C, Maunsell S, Davis T, Michaels J, Medland NA. Australian sexually transmitted infection (STI) management guidelines for use in primary care, 2022 update. Sexual Health. 2023;20(1):1-8. Available online ; https://sti.guidelines.org.au/syndromes/urethritis-penile/","Leslie SW, Ashurst JV. Nongonococcal Urethritis. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK535411/","The State of Queensland (Queensland Health). Non\u2011gonococcal urethritis (NGU) [Internet]. Last updated 7 March 2023 [cited 2025 Aug 7]. Available from: https://www.qld.gov.au/health/condition/infections-and-parasites/sexually-transmissible-infections/non-gonococcal-urethritis-ngu"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93143"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18943"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93143","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/93143"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-08-07T08:11:27+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-07T08:12:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11677"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111026"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"15","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/15"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd54","name":"Nephrology","synonyms":["Renal"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:52:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading